<paragraph pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
4. 
<taxonomicName LSID="83E7F5CE-7191-561E-B4F6-175E5455F878" authority="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sigmoidala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sigmoidala" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Sigmoidala J.Compton &amp; Schrire</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="34" pageNumber="35">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
The monospecific 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Compton &amp; B.D.Schrire, 2019" authorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" baseAuthorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sigmoidala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sigmoidala kityana" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kityana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sigmoidala kityana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has several affinities with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Roxb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara racemosa" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including the absence of bracteoles and glabrous ovaries, characters which also separate it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Endl., Gen. Pl. Suppl. 3: 104" authorityYear="1843" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Callerya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Callerya" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Callerya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">s.str.</emphasis>
which has bracteoles and sericeous ovaries. 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Compton &amp; B.D.Schrire, 2019" authorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sigmoidala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sigmoidala" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sigmoidala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pubescent floral bracts and broadly campanulate, slightly oblique, subtruncate calyx as noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schot, AM" journalOrPublisher="Blumea" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 40" refId="B91" refString="Schot, AM, 1994. A Revision of Callerya Endl. (including Padbruggea and Whitfordiodendron) (Papilionaceae: Millettieae). Blumea 39: 1 - 40" title="A Revision of Callerya Endl. (including Padbruggea and Whitfordiodendron) (Papilionaceae: Millettieae)." volume="39" year="1994">Schot (1994</bibRefCitation>
: 25) but it was placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Endl., Gen. Pl. Suppl. 3: 104" authorityYear="1843" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Callerya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Callerya" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Callerya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of the fruits that lacked the lomented endocarp. The stipules in 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Compton &amp; B.D.Schrire, 2019" authorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sigmoidala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sigmoidala" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sigmoidala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are shorter, 3-7 mm long (vs. 9-12 mm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pedicels shorter, 3-4 mm long (vs. 4-12 mm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lour., Fl. Cochinch. 2: 462" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Sarcodum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcodum" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sarcodum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), floral bracts linear, 6-8 mm long (vs. linear-lanceolate, 8-12 mm long in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 6-20 mm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lour., Fl. Cochinch. 2: 462" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Sarcodum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcodum" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sarcodum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the back of the standard densely, appressed rufous pubescent (vs. glabrous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lour., Fl. Cochinch. 2: 462" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Sarcodum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcodum" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sarcodum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the wing petals of 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Compton &amp; B.D.Schrire, 2019" authorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sigmoidala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sigmoidala" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sigmoidala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unique within Tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhu, Cathaya 6: 115 - 124" authorityYear="1994" family="Leguminosae" genus="Wisterieae" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Wisterieae" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="genus">Wisterieae</taxonomicName>
being a sigmoid shape, reflexed at the midpoint and extending outwards towards the apex (see Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 3. Sigmoidala kityana (Craib) J. Compton &amp; Schrire. A Habit B young leaf C lower surface of leaf D leaflet detail of hairs E inflorescence F flower bud with bracteole and pedicel G calyx external surface H standard petal inner surface I wing petal J keel petal K staminal column lateral view L staminal column ventral view M stamen dorsal and ventral views N ovary lateral view O style and stigma P pod Q pod detail of surface R seed ventral view S seed lateral view (all from Clark 245). Drawn by Margaret Tebbs." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.125.34877.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/313256" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">3I</figureCitation>
). The pods of 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Compton &amp; B.D.Schrire, 2019" authorityName="J. Compton &amp; Schrire" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sigmoidala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sigmoidala" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sigmoidala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are flattened, linear to obovate, 7-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 cm (vs. septate, flattened, linear, 10-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 cm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Geesink, Leiden Bot. Ser. 8: 93" authorityYear="1984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Endosamara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Endosamara" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Endosamara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and botuliform in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lour., Fl. Cochinch. 2: 462" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Sarcodum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sarcodum" order="Fabales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Sarcodum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="type species">
